By Teniola Ibitola Lagos – An Ebute Meta Magistrate’s Court in Lagos, on Tuesday, granted a 26-year-old woman, Faida Adamu, charged with alleged murder of her husband, N100,000 bail. The magistrate, Mr Alex Komolafe, granted the woman bail after she pleaded not guilty of hitting her husband, Mato Adamu, a Chief Superintendent of Customs with a pestle on the head. Komolafe granted the defendant bail with two sureties in like sum and adjourned the case until July 10 for mention. Earlier, the prosecutor, Insp Mariam Dauda, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on May 17 at 11:20 p.m. at their Gowon Estate, Ipaja, Lagos residence. Dauda alleged that the defendant used a pestle to hit Mato Adamu, 56, on his head, and he died as a result of the injuries sustained. According to the prosecutor, the offences contravene the provisions of Sections 223 and 233 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015.